{
  "image": "6641\\6641.jpg",
  "title": "The Suitcase Circus",
  "description": "URGENT: Circus acts needed! Ringmaster Gamble Christopolis is totally fine—just rebuilding his world-famous★ circus from scratch. (★It was almost famous.) With no cast and one suitcase, he’s turning to the audience for help. Chaos, comedy &amp; clowning collide. No skills required. Just show up. Please.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Christopher Gamble/Deanna Fleysher<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Deanna Fleysher<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Christopher Gamble<br/>",
  "website": "https://nobonestheatre.com",
  "plain_language": "The Suitcase Circus is a funny and heartwarming solo show about a ringmaster whose circus is gone. With just a suitcase and a big dream, he tries to put on the best show, alone, with help from the audience. This 45-minute, family-friendly show mixes clowning, physical comedy, and improv, full of laughs, surprises, and heart. It’s about imagination, resilience, and the power of play when things go wrong.",
